

Stack
-Stack class in Java implements a Stack data structure. 
-The class is based on the basic principle of last-in-first-out. 
-In addition to the basic push and pop operations, the class provides three more functions of empty, search, and peek. 
-The class can also be said to extend Vector and treats the class as a stack with the five mentioned functions. 
-The class can also be referred to as the subclass of Vector.
-It is an ordered collection that allows duplicate objects
-Insertion order is preserved
-null elements are allowed

SYNTAX:
Stack<T> variableName = new Stack<>();


Important operations of Stack
1. Adding elements
	-push() method is used to add an element to the top of the Stack.

2. Retrieving elements
	-peek() is used to retrieve or fetch the first element of the Stack which is represented at the top of the Stack.
	-peek() method does not delete or remove the element from the stack.

3.Retrieve and remove the element
	-pop() method is used to pop an element from the top of the stack and removes it.


In addition to above methods, empty() method is used to check if the Stack is empty and returns a boolean
while search(Object) method is used to check if a particular object exists in the Stack.
search() method returns the position of the object if it finds the element, -1 otherwise.